FBIS3-32100 "drlat022_b_94013" FBIS-LAT-94-022 Document Type:Daily Report 2 Feb 1994 Inter-Caribbean Affairs Haiti Increasing Adherence Noted FL0102185594 Port-au-Prince Radio Metropole in French 1145 GMT 1 Feb 94 FL0102185594 Port-au-Prince Radio Metropole Language: French Article Type:BFN [Text] A press release from the crisis committee and the presidents of the employers associations informs members and the general public that exchanges with national and international organizations, labor unions, national institutions, and the various sectors representative of the civilian society are increasing. The population is increasingly adhering to the objectives expressed in the 25 January resolution, says the press release. It states, and I quote, let us continue to reinforce our solidarity in order to save Haiti, unquote. It should be pointed out that the members of the employer sector are reportedly to meet with the members of the union sector on 1 February at the Haitian Chamber of Commerce and Industry.
